sailpoint.api.nativeidentitychange

Class NativeIdentityChangePolicyPropagator

  • java.lang.Object
    • sailpoint.api.nativeidentitychange.AbstractNativeIdentityChangePropagator
      • sailpoint.api.nativeidentitychange.NativeIdentityChangePolicyPropagator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NativeIdentityChangePropagator

    public class NativeIdentityChangePolicyPropagator
extends AbstractNativeIdentityChangePropagator
    This class provides an implementation of NativeIdentityChangePropagator that propagates NativeIdentityChangeEvents to all GenericConstraints and ActivityConstraints (which are referenced by Policies. This propagator can be used for both account and group renames.

      • getGenericConstraintIds

        protected java.util.Iterator<java.lang.String> getGenericConstraintIds(SailPointContext context,
                                                                       java.util.List<NativeIdentityChangeEvent> events)
                                                                throws GeneralException
        Gets the GenericConstraint ids that are relevant to Native Identity renaming. The only ids we care about here are those that have IdentitySelectors. The list can be further filtered by a filter string supplied via the "genericConstraintFilterString" config attribute. This filter will be ANDed with the built-in filters.
        Parameters:
        context - - the current SailPointContext
        Returns:
        List which has the GenericConstraint ids
        Throws:
        GeneralException - - if ObjectUtil.getObjectIds() fails

      • getActivityConstraintIds

        protected java.util.Iterator<java.lang.String> getActivityConstraintIds(SailPointContext context,
                                                                        java.util.List<NativeIdentityChangeEvent> events)
                                                                 throws GeneralException
        Gets the ActivityConstraint ids that are relevant to Native Identity renaming. The only ids we care about here are those that have IdentityFilters or ActivityFilters. The list can be further filtered by a filter string supplied via the "activityConstraintFilterString" config attribute. This filter will be ANDed with the built-in filters.
        Parameters:
        context - - the current SailPointContext
        Returns:
        List which has the ActivityConstraint ids
        Throws:
        GeneralException - - if ObjectUtil.getObjectIds() fails

      • processEvents

        public boolean processEvents(SailPointContext context,
                             java.util.List<NativeIdentityChangeEvent> events,
                             TaskResult result)
                      throws GeneralException
        Entrypoint for processing NativeIdentityChangeEvents with respect to propagating events throughout all Policies. The TaskResult will be updated with the number of Policies that were modified for the purpose of renaming a Native Identity. The TaskResult will also feature a breakdown of the Policies number in terms of how many were Generic Policies and how many were Activity Policies.
        Parameters:
        context - - the current SailPointContext
        events - - the List of NativeIdentityChangeEvents
        result - - the TaskResult used to store information on the number of policies and constraints that had Native Identity renames done
        Returns:
        boolean true if the event was processed
        Throws:
        GeneralException - if processConstraints() fails or if null parameters are passed in is treated by NativeIdentityChangePropagationRequestExecutor as if it were a permanent exception.
